  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b95\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0baa\u0baf \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0b95\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd  ?",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "President Gotabaya resigns today?",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Gotabaya Rajapaksa is expected to step down on Wednesday. Speaker Mahinda Yaba Abeywardana had announced that the President would announce his resignation to the people on the 13th in order to peacefully hand over the administration of the country.",
        "President Gotabaya Rajapaksa has announced his resignation following massive protests and violence in many parts of the country including the capital Colombo on the 9th. The President is expected to step down today as already announced.",
        "Regarding the unstable political situation in the country, a special party leader meeting was held on Monday under the chairmanship of Speaker Mahinda Yaba Abeywardhana.",
        "During this, it was decided to convene the parliament on the day after tomorrow, Friday after considering the ideas of all the parties, and after that on the 20th, to elect the interim president.",
        "According to the constitution, if a president resigns before the end of his term, the prime minister can take over as president, and after that, a qualified person can be elected by parliament as interim president for the remainder of the term, according to political experts.",
        "But now the protesting parties are insisting that Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe should also resign.",
        "It is also reported that if both the President and the Prime Minister have to resign, the Speaker can act as acting President until an interim President is elected.",
        "In this situation, many names have been put forward as the interim president from many sides. United People's Shakti has decided to propose the name of Opposition Leader Sajith Premadasa as the Interim President.",
        "On the other hand JVP President Anurakumara Dissanayake has announced that he is ready to take over the government. While there are various differences of opinion, President Gotabaya Rajapaksa has not directly announced any issue.",
        "In this situation, it is expected that he will resign today as he has already announced through the Speaker, and if he resigns, it will be recorded as an important event in Sri Lankan political history. It is noteworthy that Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe has said that he is ready to hand over power and resign if an all-party government is formed."
      ],
